__DESCRIPTION__

NLPW::2014::Utrecht Nederlandse Perl Workshop

by: SawyerÂ X

* Searching CPAN: Use [MetaCPAN](https://metacpan.org/)  instead of [search.cpan.org](http://search.cpan.org/)
* Inheritance: Use [parent](https://metacpan.org/pod/parent) instead of [base](https://metacpan.org/pod/base) 
* Objects: use [Moose](https://metacpan.org/pod/Moose) or [Moo](https://metacpan.org/pod/Moo), but no [Mouse](https://metacpan.org/pod/Mouse) and never [Any::Moose](https://metacpan.org/pod/Any::Moose), nor [Mo](https://metacpan.org/pod/Mo).
* Serialization: JSON, YAML, Sereal but not Storable and never XML
* HTTP User Agents: [LWP::UserAgent](https://metacpan.org/pod/LWP::UserAgent), [WWW::Mechanie](https://metacpan.org/pod/WWW::Mechanize), [HTTP::Tiny](https://metacpan.org/pod/HTTP::Tiny)
* Templates: [Template::Toolkit](https://metacpan.org/pod/Template::Toolkit) or [Xslate](https://metacpan.org/pod/Text::Xslate), but don't use [HTML::Template](https://metacpan.org/pod/HTML::Template), [Mason](https://metacpan.org/pod/Mason)
* Web: Use [PSGI](http://plackperl.org/) and not CGI.
* Threads, signals, and CPU parallel execution:


